 Rainoil Limited has said it gave prizes to winners across over 100 retail stations in its yuletide ‘Fuel and Win’ promo. In a statement yesterday, the integrated energy firm said raffle draws were conducted at the stations where winners got prizes that included generators, deep freezers, gas cookers and microwaves among others. The Head of Brand and Corporate Communications at Rainoil, Foluso Adeyemi, explained that the promo was designed to appreciate loyal customers across Nigeria’s six geo-political zones and also to draw attention to the superior quality service delivery that Rainoil has delivered to Nigerians over the years. She said, “Through this campaign, our customers have restated their commitment to the high-quality products and efficient service that we offer them. We are proud of the success of the campaign as it has offered us an opportunity to reward our growing number of customers. Hopefully, we will sustain this campaign in the coming years.” According to the statement, star winners included Fatai Abiodun (Abuja station), Mr. Benga Peters (Minna station), Salihu Zakari (Keffi station), Eze Malachi (New Nyanya station), Mr Steve-Ola-King (Ipaja station) and Alhassan Ibrahim (Ilorin station), who attested to the quality-of-service delivery of the Rainoil in all their stations. An excited star prize winner at Rainoil’s Abuja Station, Mrs. Fatai Abiodun said: “Rainoil Limited has made me happy this season. I am very excited and I don’t know what to say. I saw the advert and I decided to participate”. Another star prize winner at Ipaja in Lagos, Mr Steve  Ola-King, said he was thrilled by the experience of the fuel and win promo. According to him, this was his first time he was participating in such a promo. “I am encouraged by the gesture of the Rainoil management in putting this together. For this, I have signed my loyalty in buying fuel in their stations,” he said.